      "writtenOn": "2016-04-01T23:26:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Theoretically it may occasionally hang when recovering from sleep. In practice it won\u0027t be noticeable (finished before I login windows). And the important thing is, failing this command will also freeze the emulator and gives even worse behavior (the report here https://code.google.com/p/android/issues/detail?id\u003d204657)\n\nUnless we have a use case that the emulator intentionally fails it...\n\nInterestingly there is another issue that the input will occasionally freeze for ~30 sec when you wake up your windows. And it is not caused by the loop here.",
      "parentUuid": "2ec1e019_161cfd4d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 954,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 954,
        "endChar": 28
